                                                CIVIL RIGHTS


   USDA Mission Statement:

   To facilitate the fair and equitable treatment of USDA customers and
   employees while ensuring the delivery and enforcement of civil rights
   programs and activities.

   One World with Diversity       [diversity1.gif] [diversity2.gif]
   [diversity3.gif] [diversity5.gif]
   National Civil Rights Homepage
   [new_tiny.gif] It May Not Be Too Late For Your Complaint?
   [new_tiny.gif] Pigford Vs. Glickman: Consent Decree
   [new_tiny.gif] Latest Civil Rights Forum                Guiding
   Principles:

   We value our employees and customers and believe in the strength of
   diversity.  We are committed to treating both with dignity and
   respect.  We listen and learn.  We take pride in our abilities and are
   dedicated to contributing to the success of the USDA.  We encourage and
   reward creativity and teamwork.  We are open and honest, holding
   ourselves accountable and possessing the highest level of integrity.
   We identify the needs and expectations of our employees and customers,
   and provide quality and timely products and services.


